3rd Avenue (left), north from 36th Street. The buildings on the east side of the avenue were all torn down to make way for the construction of Gowanus Parkway, Brooklyn's northerly link in the Belt Parkway system of highways. On the west side of the avenue are the Bush Terminal buildings.

View 2 is north from 34th Street and view 3 shows a closeup of one of the Bush Terminal buildings.

October, 1940
Views 1,2,3

P. L. Sperr
